text: Patissa fulvosparsa is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Arthur Gardiner Butler in 1881. It is found in China (Shandong, Jiangxi, Guangdong, Hainan, Yunnan), Taiwan, Japan, Korea, India and Indonesia. The wingspan is about 25 mm.Japanese Moths The forewings are white with pale yellow fasciae. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1881 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Patissa fulvosparsa
